Sunrise Energy Metals Limited – High-Grade Scandium Assays Summary

(Exploration Results Announcement)

Material Information:

  • High-grade scandium intersections (600ppm cutoff):
  • 7m @ 884ppm (including 3m @ 1,123ppm)
  • 13m @ 743ppm
  • 6m @ 788ppm
  • Multiple other significant intercepts (Table 1 in announcement).
  • Drilling campaign:
  • 125 RC holes (3,589m) completed April–May 2025.
  • Targeting expansion of high-grade zones; assays pending for ~50% of samples.
  • Resource update: Results to be incorporated into an updated Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE), supporting Syerston Scandium Project feasibility study.
  • Market context: Scandium market remains tight due to China’s export restrictions (April 2025); ongoing customer discussions in alloys/semiconductors.

Key Implication:

Confirmation of high-grade scandium continuity likely to positively impact resource confidence and project economics.

Note: No capital raising, trading halt, or financial data disclosed. Focus on exploration results.

• Closure of MyDeal: Woolworths will shut down the MyDeal website by 30 September 2025, consolidating its marketplace offerings into BIG W Market and Everyday Market.
  • Financial Impact:
  • Expected cash costs: $90–100M (including equity buyout and redundancies).
  • Non-cash impairment: ~$45M.
  • Strategic Rationale: Focus on integrated retail marketplaces due to superior economics; aims to reduce Woolworths MarketPlus operating losses.
  • Forward Update: Further details on one-off costs to be provided in August 2025 (F25 results).

Omitted: Operational synergies, management quotes, non-material background.

• Acquisition Closure: Rapid Critical Metals has completed the 100% acquisition of the Prophet River Gallium-Germanium Project in British Columbia (2,110 Ha).
  • Historic Results: Previous bulk samples reported high-grade mineralization (up to 22.69% Zn, 40 g/t Ga, 1,500 ppm Ge, 0.36% Pb), highlighting strategic potential.
  • Upcoming Exploration: Planned geologic mapping and sampling (late July 2025), delayed due to wildfires. IP geophysical survey approved to aid drill target identification.
  • Strategic Significance: Ga and Ge are critical metals (banned for export by China), with applications in tech/semiconductors; project positioned as a high-value asset.

No capital raising, trading halt, or financial data disclosed.

  • 5.9m @ 0.72% Li₂O (TL24-026)

2. Capital & Strategic Updates

  • Second tranche of placement completed:
  • AUD $1.1 million raised at $0.004/share.
  • Acquisition of Amoco Antimony-Gold Project (NSW) finalized:
  • Issued 30,864,198 shares at $0.0081/share.

3. Project Positioning

  • Mavis Lake remains a strategic North American lithium asset, positioned for future market recovery.
  • 23,104m of drilling at Main Zone and 7,533m at Tot Prospect pending inclusion in updated MRE.

Note: No further drilling planned due to market conditions; focus shifts to low-cost technical work and permitting.

Next Steps: Resource expansion targeting, baseline studies, and permitting for future development readiness.

  • Dutch subsidy program: National scheme launching Autumn 2025 to support adoption of manure processing tech by 10,000–12,000 small/mid-sized farms.
  • New product development: Sprintex and Mest Water collaborating on compact compressor model for mobile ZLD systems targeting small farms.
  • Revenue milestones:
  • Deposit received: €143,250 (A$256,077) for upgraded evaluation order (now €705,000 / A$1.26M).

  • Market position: Mest Water holds exclusive EU patents and is the only approved ZLD supplier in the Netherlands.

Key Catalysts:
- Successful Van Drie Group trial (early July) for €4.8M order validation.
- Subsidy-driven demand for small-farm solutions.
